51.3	The_Stars_My_Destination	The Stars My Destination	The Stars My Destination is a science fiction novel by Alfred Bester. Originally serialized in Galaxy magazine in four parts beginning with the October 1956 issue, it first appeared in book form in the United Kingdom as Tiger! Tiger! – after William Blake's poem "The Tyger", the first verse of which is printed as the first page of the novel – and the book remains widely known under that title in markets where this edition was circulated. A working title for the novel was Hell's My Destination, and it was also associated with the name The Burning Spear.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4d/TheStarsMyDestination.jpg/224px-TheStarsMyDestination.jpg
